      <title>Bipartisan Panel Says Secret Service Needs Reform </title>
      <author>AllSides Staff</author>
      <link>https://www.allsides.com/story/defense-and-security-bipartisan-panel-says-secret-service-needs-reform</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.allsides.com/story/defense-and-security-bipartisan-panel-says-secret-service-needs-reform</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 17 Oct 2024 17:26:58 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="story-id-page-description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;An &lt;a href="https://static.foxnews.com/foxnews.com/content/uploads/2024/10/secret-service-independent-review-panel-final-report-assassination-attempt.pdf"&gt;independent review of the Secret Service&lt;/a&gt; following the &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/story/donald-trump-trump-apparently-shot-ear-rally"&gt;first assassination attempt&lt;/a&gt; on former President Donald Trump concluded the need for&amp;nbsp;"fundamental"&amp;nbsp;changes.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Details:&lt;/strong&gt; The panel, made up of government officials and former law enforcement, said that without change, what happened in Butler, PA, would happen again. The report found there was no plan to secure key buildings before the Butler rally, and there were communications breakdowns internally and with local police. The 52-page report recommended that the Secret Service de-emphasize investigating financial crimes, have overhead surveillance at outdoor events, have at least one representative of the Secret Service and state and local law enforcement at a communications hub, and bring in outside leadership. The changes should be made by March.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Quote:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;The panel &lt;a href="https://static.foxnews.com/foxnews.com/content/uploads/2024/10/secret-service-independent-review-panel-final-report-assassination-attempt.pdf"&gt;said&lt;/a&gt;,&amp;nbsp;"The Secret Service has become bureaucratic, complacent, and static even though risks have multiplied and technology has evolved."&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For Context: &lt;/strong&gt;The panel traveled to Butler, reviewed 58 multi-hour interviews of the Secret Service and law enforcement, and reviewed more than 7,000 documents. They did not find lack of funding to be one of the underlying issues. The assassination attempt in Butler led to the &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/story/defense-and-security-secret-service-director-steps-down"&gt;resignation of the Secret Service director&lt;/a&gt;. The Secret Service thwarted &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/story/donald-trump-trump-safe-after-apparent-assassination-attempt-florida"&gt;another attempt on Trump's life&lt;/a&gt; at his golf course in September.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How the Media Covered It:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Some media coverage used sensational language or subjective adjectives. &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/bbc-news-media-bias"&gt;BBC News (Center bias)&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news/2024-10-17-1042/defense-and-security-secret-service-has-deep-flaws-and-must-overhaul-leadership"&gt;said&lt;/a&gt; the report was "damning," and &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/politico-media-bias"&gt;Politico (Lean Left)&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news/2024-10-17-1037/defense-and-security-report-trump-shooting-blasts-secret-service-troubling-lack"&gt;said&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;the review&amp;nbsp;"blasts" the Secret Service.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;</description>
      <category>Defense And Security</category>
      <category>Donald Trump</category>
      <category>Trump Assassination Attempts</category>
      <category>Secret Service</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>FBI Quietly Revises 2022 Data, Showing 4.5% Rise in Violent Crime</title>
      <author>AllSides Staff</author>
      <link>https://www.allsides.com/story/violence-america-fbi-quietly-revises-2022-data-showing-45-rise-violent-crime</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.allsides.com/story/violence-america-fbi-quietly-revises-2022-data-showing-45-rise-violent-crime</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 17 Oct 2024 16:20:57 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="story-id-page-description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The FBI revised its 2022 crime data to show that violent crime rose by 4.5% in 2022. The figure stands in contrast to the “final” figure the FBI reported in September 2023, which suggested&amp;nbsp;violent crime&amp;nbsp;fell by 2.1%.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Details: &lt;/strong&gt;The change was reported by &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/real-clear-politics"&gt;RealClearPolitics (Center bias)&lt;/a&gt;, which said it “discovered the change through a &lt;a href="https://elements.visualcapitalist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/UCR_Summary_of_Crime_in_-Nation_2023.pdf"&gt;cryptic reference&lt;/a&gt; on the FBI website that states: ‘The 2022 violent crime rate has been updated for inclusion in CIUS, 2023.’” In the linked report, there is no mention that the numbers increased. RealClear reported that the only way to see the change is “by downloading the FBI’s new crime data and comparing it to the file released last year.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For Context:&lt;/strong&gt; The FBI did not mention the updated figure in its &lt;a href="https://crimeresearch.org/2024/10/the-revised-fbi-crime-data-reveals-that-it-originally-missed-1699-murders-in-2022-given-that-almost-all-murders-are-reported-how-does-the-fbi-miss-that-many-murders/"&gt;September 2024 press release&lt;/a&gt;. After this press release, which suggested&amp;nbsp;violent crime declined about 3% in 2023, many outlets&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news/2024-09-23-1115/general-news-crime-us-fell-2023-fbi-data-show"&gt;across&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news/2024-09-23-1115/politics-fbi-violent-crime-fell-2023-hate-crimes-rose"&gt;spectrum&lt;/a&gt; covered the news.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How the Media Covered It:&lt;/strong&gt; The story was covered widely by the right, and scantly by the center. AllSides did not find coverage from the left. RealClear described the FBI as having “been at the center of partisan storms.” &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/straight-arrow-news-media-bias"&gt;Straight Arrow News (Center bias)&lt;/a&gt; described “the issue of violent crime in the United States” as “politically charged.” &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/fox-news-media-bias"&gt;Fox News (Right bias)&lt;/a&gt; reported speaking to a Biden administration official who said the FBI “often adjusts crime estimates as more data is reported.”&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;</description>
      <category>Violence In America</category>
      <category>Crime</category>
      <category>FBI</category>
      <category>Journalism</category>
      <category>Media Bias</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Fact Checking Harris and Trump’s Fox News Interviews</title>
      <author>AllSides Staff</author>
      <link>https://www.allsides.com/story/facts-and-fact-checking-fact-checking-harris-and-trump-s-fox-news-interviews</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.allsides.com/story/facts-and-fact-checking-fact-checking-harris-and-trump-s-fox-news-interviews</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 17 Oct 2024 13:58:15 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="story-id-page-description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, former President Trump and Vice President Harris engaged in separate TV interviews with &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/fox-news-media-bias"&gt;Fox News (Right bias)&lt;/a&gt;, drawing fact check coverage.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For Context:&lt;/strong&gt; Harris appeared in an ostensibly pre-recorded &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/story/2024-presidential-election-harris-interviewed-fox-news"&gt;27-minute interview with host Bret Baier&lt;/a&gt;. Trump appeared in a 60-minute town hall with host Harris Faulkner, where he answered questions from an all-female audience.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;From the Left:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/facts-first-cnn-media-bias"&gt;CNN Fact Check (Left bias)&lt;/a&gt; fact checked Trump’s town hall. It wrote, “He told a bunch of lies,” and presented 19 claims Trump made that it said were false. Key claims examined included statements Trump made about immigration, abortion, the economy, and foreign affairs.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;From the Right:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/washington-examiner"&gt;Washington Examiner (Lean Right bias)&lt;/a&gt; described Harris’ claim that “Trump was responsible for making taxpayer-funded sex change surgeries ‘available’ to federal inmates.” The Examiner noted a case where a transgender inmate sued the White House, receiving pushback from Trump, but eventually acquiescence from the Biden administration. &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/washington-free-beacon"&gt;The Washington Free Beacon (Right bias)&lt;/a&gt; also published an analysis in which it accused Harris of dodging live “fact checks and follow ups” from Baier during the interview.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;</description>
      <category>2024 Presidential Election</category>
      <category>Politics</category>
      <category>Donald Trump</category>
      <category>Kamala Harris</category>
      <category>Fox News</category>
      <category>Bret Baier</category>
      <category>Facts And Fact Checking</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Harris Interviewed By Fox News</title>
      <author>AllSides Staff</author>
      <link>https://www.allsides.com/story/2024-presidential-election-harris-interviewed-fox-news</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.allsides.com/story/2024-presidential-election-harris-interviewed-fox-news</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 16 Oct 2024 23:31:49 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="story-id-page-description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Vice President Kamala Harris sat down with Bret Baier of &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/fox-news-media-bias"&gt;Fox News (Right bias)&lt;/a&gt; for a 27-minute interview that aired Wednesday evening.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Highlights&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul&gt;  	&lt;li&gt;For the first 10 minutes, Baier asked Harris about how President Joe Biden's administration handled&amp;nbsp;immigration policy, suggesting&amp;nbsp;it had failed to appropriately deter unauthorized immigration.&amp;nbsp;Harris countered that the administration was more willing to solve immigration problems than Donald Trump,&amp;nbsp;pointing&amp;nbsp;to its support of a&amp;nbsp;border security&amp;nbsp;bill that&amp;nbsp;failed after Trump encouraged congressional Republicans to vote against it.&lt;/li&gt;  	&lt;li&gt;When asked what she'd do differently than Biden, Harris highlighted her&amp;nbsp;housing policy&amp;nbsp;proposals and said she offered a chance to move on&amp;nbsp;from Trump's "divisive rhetoric." Baier questioned how Harris was "turning the page" despite having&amp;nbsp;"been in office for three and a half years."&amp;nbsp;Harris responded by listing former Trump administration officials who have called him "unfit to serve," "unstable" and "dangerous."&lt;/li&gt;  	&lt;li&gt;Baier asked if Harris had concerns about Biden's&amp;nbsp;"mental faculties." Harris said Biden had the&amp;nbsp;"judgement and experience"&amp;nbsp;to make "important decisions," but also that "Joe Biden is not on the ballot, and Donald Trump is."&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How the Media Covered It&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/hill-media-bias"&gt;The Hill (Center)&lt;/a&gt; spotlighted the &lt;a href="https://thehill.com/homenews/campaign/4937635-kamala-harris-bret-baier-fox-news-interview/"&gt;immigration exchange&lt;/a&gt;, while &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/fox-business-media-bias"&gt;Fox Business (Lean Right)&lt;/a&gt; featured the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="http://www.foxbusiness.com/media/vp-kamala-harris-responds-why-more-americans-trust-trump-economy"&gt;economic policy questions&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/national-review"&gt;National Review (Lean Right)&lt;/a&gt; said Harris "&lt;a href="https://www.nationalreview.com/news/harris-stumbles-through-fox-interview-insists-her-presidency-will-turn-the-page/"&gt;stumbled&lt;/a&gt;" and "had trouble answering questions." &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/abc-news-media-bias"&gt;ABC (Lean Left)&lt;/a&gt; called the interview "&lt;a href="https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/harris-paints-trump-national-threat-testy-fox-news/story?id=114869202"&gt;combative&lt;/a&gt;" and focused on Harris' critiques of Trump for undemocratic actions. &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/daily-beast-media-bias"&gt;Daily Beast (Left)&lt;/a&gt; said Baier "&lt;a href="https://www.thedailybeast.com/kamala-harris-shuts-down-bret-baier-as-he-plays-the-maga-hits-in-fox-news-interview"&gt;played the MAGA hits&lt;/a&gt;."&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;</description>
      <category>2024 Presidential Election</category>
      <category>Kamala Harris</category>
      <category>Fox News</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Harris Accused of Plagiarizing Parts of &amp;#039;Smart on Crime&amp;#039; Book</title>
      <author>AllSides Staff</author>
      <link>https://www.allsides.com/story/2024-presidential-election-harris-accused-plagiarizing-parts-smart-crime-book</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.allsides.com/story/2024-presidential-election-harris-accused-plagiarizing-parts-smart-crime-book</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 16 Oct 2024 20:05:53 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="story-id-page-description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Chris Rufo, a conservative activist and&amp;nbsp;senior fellow at the &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/manhattan-institute"&gt;Manhattan Institute (Lean Right bias)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://christopherrufo.com/p/kamala-harriss-plagiarism-problem"&gt;highlighted an analysis&lt;/a&gt; from&amp;nbsp;Austrian "plagiarism hunter"&amp;nbsp;Dr. Stefan Weber in which Weber says&amp;nbsp;Harris' co-written 2009 book&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Smart on Crime: A Career Prosecutor's Plan to Make Us Safer&lt;/em&gt; contained 27 instances of plagiarism.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Details:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Weber alleged&amp;nbsp;that throughout the 248-page book,&amp;nbsp;"24 fragments are plagiarism from other authors, [and] 3 fragments are self-plagiarism from a work written with a co-author." Several times, he alleges, they pulled verbatim text from a source without using quotation marks. In another instance, he said "Kamala Harris fabricated a source reference, inventing a nonexistent page number. The self-promotional content from Goodwill Industries was copied verbatim without citing the source."&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How the Media Covered It:&lt;/strong&gt; The story was covered widely on the right and less&amp;nbsp;on the left. &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/new-york-times"&gt;The New York Times (Lean Left)&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news/2024-10-15-0835/2024-presidential-election-conservative-activist-seizes-passages-harris-book"&gt;downplayed&lt;/a&gt; the allegations, naming only five of the examples Rufo cited without mentioning the other cases, and adding that the publisher of Plagiarism Today said that the "errors were not serious." He later said, "I was unaware of a full dossier with additional allegations, which led some to accuse the New York Times of withholding that information from me. However, the article clearly stated that it was my ‘initial reaction’ to those allegations, not a complete analysis," and added&amp;nbsp;that the allegations were "more serious" than he initially believed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;</description>
      <category>2024 Presidential Election</category>
      <category>Kamala Harris</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>How Trump and Harris Are Courting Men and Women Voters</title>
      <author>AllSides Staff</author>
      <link>https://www.allsides.com/story/2024-presidential-election-how-trump-and-harris-are-courting-men-and-women-voters</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.allsides.com/story/2024-presidential-election-how-trump-and-harris-are-courting-men-and-women-voters</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 16 Oct 2024 19:00:42 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="story-id-page-description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Polling shows that former President Trump is struggling to gain support from women, while Harris is &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news/2024-10-16-1235/2024-presidential-election-democrats-fear-harris-losing-too-many-male-voters"&gt;struggling to gain&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;support from men.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Data:&lt;/strong&gt; An &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/nbc-news-media-bias"&gt;NBC News (Lean Left bias)&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://s3.documentcloud.org/documents/25201760/240478-nbc-october-2024-poll_101324-release.pdf"&gt;poll&lt;/a&gt; has&amp;nbsp;men going 56-40% for Trump and women going 55-41% for Harris. NBC analyst Steve Kornacki &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news/2024-10-16-1210/2024-presidential-election-nbcs-kornacki-gender-gap-favors-trump-new-poll-trump"&gt;said&lt;/a&gt;, "Trump is up 16 among men, Harris up 14 among women, that is a 30-point difference between them, and if that happens on election day, that's one for the history books and we've never seen it that high." A &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/new-york-times"&gt;New York Times (Lean Left)&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2024/10/13/us/elections/times-siena-poll-likely-electorate-crosstabs.html"&gt;poll&lt;/a&gt; has Trump up 11% among men and Harris up 15% among women.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Harris: &lt;/strong&gt;Harris has unveiled recent policy proposals to &lt;a href="https://x.com/bakari_sellers/status/1845780349684453721?s=46&amp;amp;t=xIfOM5Jozzf86lpB-yGRqQ"&gt;appeal&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news/2024-10-16-1216/2024-presidential-election-harris-outreach-black-men-new-policy-interviews"&gt;black men&lt;/a&gt;, including legalizing marijuana, investing in mentorship and apprenticeship programs, launching a National Health Equity Initiative, and providing up to&amp;nbsp;$20,000 in "fully forgivable" loans to black business owners. She has also &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news/2024-10-15-1041/2024-presidential-election-harris-could-join-joe-rogan-podcast-hunt-male-votes"&gt;discussed appearing&lt;/a&gt; on the Joe Rogan Experience podcast to reach male voters.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trump:&lt;/strong&gt; In his appeal to women voters, Trump held a town hall on &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news-source/fox-news-media-bias"&gt;Fox News (Right)&lt;/a&gt; with an all-women audience on Oct. 15 (aired on Oct. 16). He &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news/2024-10-16-1220/2024-presidential-election-fox-news-faulkner-focus-hosts-women-only-trump-town"&gt;discussed&lt;/a&gt; border security, the economy, IVF and abortion, transgender issues, and foreign policy.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How the Media Covered It:&lt;/strong&gt; Some voices on the right focused on Trump's &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news/2024-10-16-1230/2024-presidential-election-quite-surprising-cnn-s-harry-enten-says-trump"&gt;surge among&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news/2024-10-16-1232/2024-presidential-election-why-historic-numbers-black-men-me-are-voting-trump"&gt;men&lt;/a&gt;, while the left &lt;a href="https://vanjones.substack.com/p/what-black-men-need-from-kamala"&gt;emphasized&lt;/a&gt; Harris' &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news/2024-10-16-1228/2024-presidential-election-harris-works-energize-black-male-voters-while-trump"&gt;outreach to black men&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news/2024-10-16-1226/2024-presidential-election-they-ve-given-idea-they-can-get-women-how-trump"&gt;Trump's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news/2024-10-16-1223/2024-presidential-election-donald-trump-trying-soften-his-image-women-voters-it"&gt;lack of appeal&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.allsides.com/news/2024-10-16-1224/2024-presidential-election-trump-held-town-hall-talk-women-s-issues-across-us"&gt;to women&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;</description>
      <category>2024 Presidential Election</category>
      <category>Women's Issues</category>
      <category>Donald Trump</category>
      <category>Kamala Harris</category>
      <category>Women</category>
